(661, 69, 'page_title', 'Helping  exceptional skiers reach the top'),
(662, 69, '_page_title', 'field_55049e9271a61'),
(663, 69, 'secondary_title', 'How Mike & Manny are using skiing as  a way to connect with and inspire the next generation of Canadian youth.'),
(664, 69, '_secondary_title', 'field_55049eb171a62'),
(665, 69, 'page_intro', 'Mike & Manny were supported in all areas on their road up the mountain in competitive ski racing which instilled a strong value of giving back to the sport and community that has given them so much. Their community helped them live out their dreams and when they found themselves in a position to return this favour, they found it absolutely necessary to do so. This began with a bursary program for four enthusiastic young ski racers from BC.\r\n\r\nThat following spring the two Canadian National Ski Team and World Cup racers launched the annual Cowboy Ski Camp, an all expenses paid four-day signature event that provides coaching, and ski training to up and coming athletes. The Cowboy camp offers a special mixture of passion, work and fun to inspire the \r\nathletes to see that their dreams are possible. Mike and Manny saw the power that came from sharing their love of skiing with others and in 2014 in conjunction \r\nwith Grouse Mountain and Big Brothers, expanded outside of the ski racing community to launch an annual Community Ski Day for 20 big and little brothers. With ski racing their passion, skiing has become the vehicle to give back to the next generation, inspiringthem so they too can live their dreams. This is our story.'),
(666, 69, '_page_intro', 'field_55049eca71a63'),
